description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Mental Capacity Act &amp; Deprivation of Liberty Assessor&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Part time – 15 hours per week&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Band 6&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Berkshire West CCG is looking for a motivated qualified professional person with a drive and commitment to promotingMental Capacity Act and Safeguarding Adults to join our safeguarding team. The key function will be to coordinate and undertake the work required for Deprivation of Liberty assessments to besubmitted to the Court of Protection for all relevant CCG health funded placements within community settings. This role will include gathering information from records and providers and an ability to analysis the information in the context of the Mental Capacity Act&amp; Deprivation of Liberty Safeguardinglegislation. You will be required toundertake mental capacity assessments, liaise with key professionals, families and friends involved in an individual’s care and to chair best Interest meetings and reviews forthe deprivation of liberty cases.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;It is an exciting and changing time ahead for deprivation of liberty with the new Liberty Protection Safeguards planned implementation in 2022 and this new role within the CCG will be part of the ongoing development. This post offers flexible working arrangements across the week and may be combined with other part time post or consultancy work. The position is permanent andsupervision will be provided. We welcome applications from people with experience inworking with MentalCapacity and best interest assessments. There will be an opportunity to discuss training as a Best Interest Assessor for the successful candidate after an induction period. We would like to hear from you if you are interested in the position and working autonomously within a team. We welcome applications as a secondment and would ask that you discuss this with your employer to seek support for any secondment request.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The postholer will require a clean driving licence and enhanced DBS checks as part of safer recruitment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We look forward to hearing from you for an informal discussion please contact Kathy Kelly Designated Head of SafeguardingAdults on Mon – Fri 8.30 -5.30 on07920 860047 or Kathykelly@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Interviews will take place on 30th November 2020.&lt;/p&gt;
